{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The I\/O Kit is a set of system frameworks and libraries for creating device drivers on Mac OS X, supporting both 32 and 64 bit architectures. Learn about the design of I\/O Kit drivers, as well as tips and tricks for fast, efficient driver development and debugging. Whether you’re bringing a new device to Mac OS X or developing an application to access an existing device, this session is for you."}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-203-io-kit-device-drivers-for-mac-os-x"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by reading the transcript and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-203-IO-Kit-Device-Drivers-for-Mac-OS-X","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC10","title":"I\/O Kit Device Drivers for Mac OS X"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Read Transcript","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/203\/","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"sections":[],"references":{"WWDC10.jpeg":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC10.jpeg","alt":null},"WWDC10-Icon.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWD